title: Grateful Dead Live at The Spectrum on 1989-10-18
description: Shakedown Street, Little Red Rooster, El Paso, Queen Jane Approximately, Bird Song, The Music Never Stopped China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider, Ship of Fools, Women Are Smarter, Terrapin Station-> Drums-> Jam-> Gimme Some Lovin'-> All Along The Watchtower-> Black Peter-> Around & Around-> Good Lovin', E: U.S. Blues

reviews.review_text: Geoood! I got an SBD copy of this show off of another music archive site. The Bird Song first set is amazing better wear a seatbelt for that one and put on some fresh underwear.
Great Shakedown From the get the boys are on,great show.Great sound on these audience recordings
10/18/89 Jerry rips it up on 'Rider,and rest of show is well played.Hot Terrapin ! Good AUD quality.

the ULTIMATE shakedown agree 100% with previous comment. My favorite shakedown of all time! Download this show! I am biased becuase this was my first show, but putting that aside, it's pretty much the jazziest and most "on" I've ever heard jerry and the boys for this song (rest of the show is great too...wonderful peggy-o, queen jane, and entire second set). By the middle of Jerry's first shorter solo in shakedown (before the very extended jam after the verses) it's clear he's on fire. Jer, I can't say how much I miss seeing you play live.

Awesome, Awesome Show! I've been to many shows and listened to hundreds more and this is a definitive example of the boys at their best!  Shakedown, Music, Rider, Terrapin & Black Peter all rip!  Kick back and enjoy - the matrix recordings are a lil better than this one but if you want to download this is the one to go with!
